This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with topic modeling and automatic topic labeling algorithms. It could also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as topic modeling is often used in information retrieval tasks. Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) are also likely sub-categories as topic modeling is a popular technique in these fields. Finally, it could belong to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as topic modeling is often used in analyzing social networks and online communities.
